## Part 3: Macro Implementation Details

The macro should handle types in this order:

### 3.1 Primitives
Check if type matches known primitives, return existing val:
```scala
if (tpe =:= typeOf[Int]) '{ Binding.Primitive.int }
else if (tpe =:= typeOf[String]) '{ Binding.Primitive.string }
// ... etc for all primitives
```

### 3.2 DynamicValue
```scala
if (tpe =:= typeOf[DynamicValue]) '{ Binding.Dynamic() }
```

### 3.3 Option, Either, None, Some, Left, Right
Use existing factory methods:
```scala
if (tpe <:< typeOf[Option[_]]) {
  val elemTpe = typeArgs(tpe).head
  if (tpe =:= typeOf[None.type]) '{ Binding.Record.none }
  else if (tpe <:< typeOf[Some[_]]) /* use specialized or generic some */
  else '{ Binding.Variant.option[elemTpe] }
}
```

### 3.4 Known Collection Types (List, Vector, Set, Map, etc.)
For concrete collection types like `List[Int]`:
```scala
if (tpe <:< typeOf[List[_]]) {
  '{ Binding.of[List].asInstanceOf[Binding.Seq[List, ${elemTpe}]] }
}
```

### 3.5 Array and IArray
Special-case with inline constructor generation (copy logic from Schema macro).

### 3.6 Smart Constructor / Opaque / Newtype Detection
Check for companion `apply` returning `Either[E, A]`:
```scala
def hasSmartConstructor(tpe: Type): Option[(Type, Symbol)] = {
  val companion = tpe.typeSymbol.companion
  companion.typeSignature.member(TermName("apply")) match {
    case method: MethodSymbol =>
      method.returnType match {
        case TypeRef(_, sym, List(errTpe, resultTpe)) if sym == typeOf[Either[_, _]].typeSymbol =>
          if (resultTpe =:= tpe) Some((method.paramLists.head.head.typeSignature, method))
          else None
        case _ => None
      }
    case _ => None
  }
}
```

If detected, generate `Binding.Wrapper`:
```scala
'{
  new Binding.Wrapper[A, Underlying](
    wrap = { underlying =>
      ${companion}.apply(underlying) match {
        case Right(a) => Right(a)
        case Left(e: SchemaError) => Left(e)
        case Left(e) => Left(SchemaError.invalidValue(DynamicOptic.root.nodes.toList, e.toString))
      }
    },
    unwrap = _.${extractorField}
  )
}
```

### 3.7 ZIO Prelude Newtypes
Use baked-in knowledge:
- Check if type matches `TypeRef(compTpe, "Type")` where companion extends `zio.prelude.Newtype`
- Dealias to underlying type
- Generate Wrapper with Newtype.wrap/unwrap

### 3.8 Scala 3 Opaque Types
- Check `isOpaqueAlias`
- Dealias via `translucentSuperType`
- Check for smart constructor in companion
- Generate Wrapper

### 3.9 Sealed Traits / Enums
Generate `Binding.Variant`:
```scala
'{
  new Binding.Variant[A](
    discriminator = new Discriminator[A] {
      def discriminate(a: A): Int = a match {
        case _: Subtype1 => 0
        case _: Subtype2 => 1
        // ...
      }
    },
    matchers = Matchers(
      new Matcher[Subtype1] { def downcastOrNull(a: Any) = ... },
      new Matcher[Subtype2] { def downcastOrNull(a: Any) = ... },
      // ...
    )
  )
}
```

### 3.10 Case Classes / Products
Generate `Binding.Record`:
```scala
'{
  new Binding.Record[A](
    constructor = new Constructor[A] {
      def usedRegisters: RegisterOffset = ${computedOffset}
      def construct(in: Registers, offset: RegisterOffset): A = {
        new A(
          in.getInt(offset),      // for Int field
          in.getObject(offset + 4).asInstanceOf[String], // for String field
          // ...
        )
      }
    },
    deconstructor = new Deconstructor[A] {
      def usedRegisters: RegisterOffset = ${computedOffset}
      def deconstruct(out: Registers, offset: RegisterOffset, in: A): Unit = {
        out.setInt(offset, in.field1)
        out.setObject(offset + 4, in.field2)
        // ...
