- `schema/shared/src/main/scala-3/zio/blocks/schema/SchemaCompanionVersionSpecific.scala`
- `schema/shared/src/main/scala-2/zio/blocks/schema/SchemaCompanionVersionSpecific.scala`

Replace inline binding generation with calls to `Binding.of[T]`:

```scala
// BEFORE (example for case class):
new Schema(
  reflect = new Reflect.Record[Binding, T](
    fields = Vector($fields*),
    typeName = $tpeName,
    recordBinding = new Binding.Record(
      constructor = new Constructor { ... },
      deconstructor = new Deconstructor { ... }
    ),
    ...
  )
)

// AFTER:
new Schema(
  reflect = new Reflect.Record[Binding, T](
    fields = Vector($fields*),
    typeName = $tpeName,
    recordBinding = Binding.of[T].asInstanceOf[Binding.Record[T]],
    ...
  )
)
```

Note: Schema macro still handles Reflect structure, TypeName derivation, field traversal, etc. Only binding creation is delegated.

